  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are international laws and agreements aimed at preventing money laundering. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) is the primary international organization that sets standards and promotes policies to combat money laundering and terrorist financing. Many countries have adopted anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations based on FATF recommendations, which include:\n\n1. Requiring financial institutions to conduct customer due diligence\n2. Maintaining transaction records\n3. Reporting suspicious activities\n4. Implementing Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n5. Establishing legal frameworks to prosecute money laundering\n\nThe United Nations and international organizations like the World Bank also support these efforts through various conventions and guidelines.",
